sections.text:
In all classes, subject to the special provisions for each class and the tolerances allowed, the chanterelles must be: 
- intact; the stalk must be attached to the cap; the earth-soiled foot can be cut;
- sound; produce affected by rotting or deterioration such as to make it unfit for consumption is excluded;
- clean; practically free of any visible foreign matter;
- positively identifiable;
- firm;
- fresh in appearance;
- practically free from pests;
- practically free from damage caused by pests;
- free of abnormal external moisture; and
- free of any foreign smell and/or taste.
The development and condition of the chanterelles must be such as to enable them to:
- withstand transportation and handling; and
- arrive in satisfactory condition at the place of destination.

